1
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:17,300
<i>Jessica,
I just have one last wish.</i>

2
00:00:17,567 --> 00:00:19,867
<i>Maybe you could visit me
in my dreams.</i>

3
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,267
<i> I love you, Dad.</i>

4
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:22,867
<i> Can you give me a hug?</i>

5
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:26,567
<i> Thank you so much, Jessica.</i>

6
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:28,033
<i> I love you so much, sweetie.</i>

7
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:30,767
<i>This is my favorite photo
of Jessica.</i>

8
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:32,133
<i> This is the only copy I have.</i>

9
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:33,733
<i>- What about you?
-4 Don't worry about me.</i>

10
00:00:33,900 --> 00:00:35,633
<i>You have no memories of Jessica.</i>

11
00:00:35,867 --> 00:00:36,433
<i>While I have a lot to remember
her by.</i>

12
00:00:36,567 --> 00:00:37,867
<i> Alice, help me.</i>

13
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,333
<i>I can't do this anymore.
You're the only one I have.</i>

14
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:43,167
<i> Go ahead, try to turn on me.</i>

15
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:44,833
<i>What are you going to do?
You'll take me down with you?</i>

16
00:00:44,967 --> 00:00:47,667
<i>You have no evidence against me.</i>

17
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:49,067
<i> Alice!</i>

18
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:51,767
<i>You have been served a summons
from the Regional Trial Court.</i>

19
00:00:54,167 --> 00:00:56,067
<i> Annulment?</i>

20
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:59,233
<i>I have known Felma and
Manuel for many years.</i>

21
00:01:00,933 --> 00:01:03,533
<i>And I know their love
story very well.</i>

22
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:06,167
<i>God destined them to be
together until the end.</i>

23
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,900
<i>I finally fulfilled
my promise to you.</i>

24
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:10,633
<i> To marry you.</i>

25
00:01:10,767 --> 00:01:12,400
<i> From now on,</i>

26
00:01:12,700 --> 00:01:15,567
<i> you will only be the one...</i>

27
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:17,567
<i> and only Mrs. Cruz.</i>

28
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:35,233
Alright, everyone,
before I continue the merriment,

29
00:01:35,533 --> 00:01:38,500
may I invite
all the single ladies

30
00:01:38,633 --> 00:01:41,667
to gather for the bouquet toss!

31
00:01:41,833 --> 00:01:45,800
Come on! Don't be shy.
Come on, come over here.

32
00:01:45,933 --> 00:01:49,867
What about the girls over there?
Come on over here!

33
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,833
There you go, perfect!

34
00:01:51,967 --> 00:01:54,100
Let's all gather here.

35
00:01:54,233 --> 00:01:58,000
What about over here?
Who's single over here?

36
00:01:58,133 --> 00:02:01,567
There you go!
There she is, she's gorgeous!

37
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:04,333
Come on, don't be shy.
Okay, again...

38
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:09,167
Before we start, I'd like to see
your beautiful smiles.

39
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,733
Can you please show us
your beautiful smiles!

40
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:14,367
There you go!

41
00:02:14,533 --> 00:02:20,233
Well, this is the celebration of
unity, commitment, and love.

42
00:02:20,367 --> 00:02:26,167
And this is the wedding
reception of Mr. and Mrs. Cruz!

43
00:02:26,300 --> 00:02:30,467
Can we give a round of applause
for everyone here?

44
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:34,467
There you go.
Look at all our gorgeous guests.

45
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:36,233
Are you all ready?

46
00:02:36,533 --> 00:02:39,867
- Okay, I want to hear! Louder!
- Yes!

47
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,667
Perfect! Beautiful!

48
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:51,300
A big round of applause for our
newlywed. Mr. and Mrs. Cruz!

49
00:02:51,467 --> 00:02:52,700
There you go!

50
00:02:52,833 --> 00:02:55,767
There you go.
Look at all our gorgeous guests.

51
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:57,600
Are you ready?

52
00:02:58,633 --> 00:03:02,600
There you go. One, two, three!

53
00:03:02,733 --> 00:03:04,633
Out! Everyone out!

54
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:08,000
Everyone! Go outside!
Come on, we have to go out!

55
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:09,533
Get out!

56
00:03:09,667 --> 00:03:11,267
Out! Everybody!

57
00:03:11,533 --> 00:03:13,800
Go outside!

58
00:03:13,933 --> 00:03:16,067
Take your kids!

59
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:18,033
Get the kids out!

60
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:23,533
Hurry! Get out, now!

61
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:27,700
Get out, now!

62
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:29,600
Manuel, the kids!

63
00:03:30,567 --> 00:03:32,033
Noah, where's Felma!

64
00:03:32,167 --> 00:03:33,433
I'm not leaving without Mom!
Where is she?

65
00:03:33,567 --> 00:03:36,833
Go on? Get out of here!
We'll look for her!

66
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:39,233
Go on, we'll find your mom!

67
00:03:39,367 --> 00:03:40,867
Mom!

68
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,533
Felma!

69
00:03:59,067 --> 00:04:00,933
- Where's Manuel?
- Water please!

70
00:04:01,067 --> 00:04:01,867
- What?
- Water.

71
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,433
Water? I'll get some water.

72
00:04:03,567 --> 00:04:06,933
Watch them, okay?

73
00:04:07,067 --> 00:04:09,667
I'm just going to get some help.

74
00:04:10,933 --> 00:04:12,167
My kids!

75
00:04:13,333 --> 00:04:14,700
Manuel!

76
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,100
Wait, wait, wait here.

77
00:04:18,233 --> 00:04:20,700
I need to find
my kids and Manuel.

78
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:23,933
Manuel, wait, I'm okay now.

79
00:04:25,433 --> 00:04:26,700
Hazel?

80
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:28,100
Surprise.

81
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:29,633
I'm back.

82
00:04:36,233 --> 00:04:37,433
Jeffrey!

83
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:38,767
Let's go.

84
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:41,133
Andrea. Where's Mom?

85
00:04:41,267 --> 00:04:43,033
Mom?

86
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:44,900
Mom?

87
00:04:47,567 --> 00:04:49,433
Where's Tetay?

88
00:04:49,567 --> 00:04:50,933
Andrea!

89
00:04:51,067 --> 00:04:52,533
Coleen!

90
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:54,200
Tetay, sweetie!

91
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:55,133
Daisy.

92
00:04:55,267 --> 00:04:58,400
Auntie, my mom!
My mom is missing.

93
00:04:58,533 --> 00:04:59,333
Where's Mom?

94
00:04:59,467 --> 00:05:00,433
- I don't know.
- Mom!

95
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,067
Where's Mom?

96
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,367
Manuel!

97
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:04,867
Felma!

98
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,700
Manuel! She's probably outside.
Come on!

99
00:05:07,867 --> 00:05:10,067
Felma!

100
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,867
- Let go of me! Help!
- Go ahead...

101
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:14,800
yell for help,
I'll slit your throat!

102
00:05:15,933 --> 00:05:18,100
Come on, now!

103
00:05:18,233 --> 00:05:20,467
Where's Mom and Dad?

104
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:22,233
Manuel!

105
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:24,000
Dad!

106
00:05:24,133 --> 00:05:25,400
Where's Mom?

107
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:26,600
She's not with you?

108
00:05:26,733 --> 00:05:28,233
She's not here.

109
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:29,867
Where is she?

110
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,867
Felma!

111
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,267
Felma!

112
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,300
Felma!

113
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:37,367
Felma!

114
00:05:38,667 --> 00:05:41,000
Stop fussing!

115
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:44,433
Abel!

116
00:05:45,033 --> 00:05:46,267
Go ahead, call for help.

117
00:05:46,533 --> 00:05:49,867
Call him,
and I will slit your throat!

118
00:05:55,867 --> 00:05:57,867
Hurry up!

119
00:05:58,167 --> 00:05:59,933
Sir, hurry up!

120
00:06:00,067 --> 00:06:02,800
- Don't make any noise!
- Help!

121
00:06:02,933 --> 00:06:05,767
- Hurry.
- Help us!

122
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:07,100
Didang!

123
00:06:11,567 --> 00:06:13,033
Ma'am Felma?

124
00:06:14,033 --> 00:06:15,367
Is that Hazel?

125
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,367
Ma'am Felma?

126
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:27,800
Ma'am Felma?

127
00:06:27,933 --> 00:06:29,233
Ma'am Felma?

128
00:06:30,633 --> 00:06:32,000
Ma'am Felma?

129
00:06:32,133 --> 00:06:33,400
Be quiet.

130
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,200
Ma'am Felma, Ma'am Felma!

131
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:39,067
Ma'am Felma?

132
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:40,533
Ma'am Felma?

133
00:06:43,367 --> 00:06:44,533
Ma'am Felma?

134
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,000
Wait!

135
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:58,033
Manuel!

136
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,333
Hurry up!

137
00:07:07,467 --> 00:07:08,433
Manuel!

138
00:07:09,733 --> 00:07:10,967
Help me!

139
00:07:12,167 --> 00:07:13,733
Don't even try it!

140
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,000
I'm warning you!

141
00:07:16,067 --> 00:07:17,800
Try it.

142
00:07:17,933 --> 00:07:19,600
Wait! I said wait!

143
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:31,033
Help!

144
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:37,933
Get out!

145
00:07:39,467 --> 00:07:40,500
My phone!

146
00:07:40,633 --> 00:07:41,800
Leave it behind, let's go!

147
00:07:41,933 --> 00:07:43,100
Help!

148
00:08:06,833 --> 00:08:08,167
One year!

149
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:11,900
I prepared for a year
for this moment!

150
00:08:12,933 --> 00:08:16,067
Every day and night,

151
00:08:16,533 --> 00:08:18,867
I give up everything I have.

152
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,367
All of it,

153
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,867
just to get back at you!

154
00:08:23,033 --> 00:08:24,300
Get in line!

155
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:27,000
Do it properly.

156
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:29,200
Count down now.

157
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:30,900
- One.
- Two.

158
00:08:31,033 --> 00:08:32,167
- Three.
- Four.

159
00:08:32,300 --> 00:08:33,467
- Five.
- Six.

160
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:34,733
- Seven.
- Eight.

161
00:08:34,867 --> 00:08:37,067
- Nine.
- Ten, the last number.

162
00:08:43,767 --> 00:08:44,633
What was that?

163
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:47,833
What's going on?

164
00:08:54,767 --> 00:08:57,000
- I can't breathe!
- Help!

165
00:08:58,867 --> 00:09:00,067
I can't breathe!

166
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:20,233
I kept my eyes on you.

167
00:09:21,733 --> 00:09:23,800
Remember Alonso?

168
00:09:23,933 --> 00:09:26,467
He's always there,
always watching.

169
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,900
Always getting updated.

170
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:29,900
I know everything that's
going on in your life.

171
00:09:30,033 --> 00:09:31,000
Do you know that?

172
00:09:31,233 --> 00:09:35,333
Even on your wedding day,
I know every detail of it.

173
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:39,533
That's why I made sure
that I could escape.

174
00:09:39,667 --> 00:09:42,233
To get to you!

175
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:44,067
Look at us now!

176
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,433
See.

177
00:09:47,633 --> 00:09:49,067
Look!

178
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:51,367
I came prepared.

179
00:09:51,833 --> 00:09:54,933
I saw how you stole

180
00:09:56,367 --> 00:09:59,167
my title as Mrs. Cruz!

181
00:09:59,433 --> 00:10:03,767
That's why I'm here
to erase you from this world!

182
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,933
You cried on our wedding
day, too, Manuel.

183
00:10:17,067 --> 00:10:18,767
But it's different this time.

184
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:20,667
You're happy.

185
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:22,200
Unlike before.

186
00:10:22,333 --> 00:10:23,367
Manuel Cruz.

187
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:26,367
If you freely
and voluntarily consent

188
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:29,600
to be united in marriage
to Hazel Capistrano...

189
00:10:29,733 --> 00:10:30,833
I do.

190
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:37,633
I have known Felma and Manuel
for many years.

191
00:10:39,467 --> 00:10:42,067
And I know their
love story.

192
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:47,033
It's complicated
and full of challenges.

193
00:10:47,167 --> 00:10:49,433
But look at them now.

194
00:10:49,567 --> 00:10:53,733
They're back together again, and
God meant them to be together.

195
00:10:53,867 --> 00:10:57,767
And I'm grateful to
unite them today.

196
00:10:58,033 --> 00:11:01,633
So Manuel and Felma,

197
00:11:01,767 --> 00:11:04,733
you can speak your vows
to one another.

198
00:11:22,833 --> 00:11:24,167
Don't worry,
I'm not going to spit on you.

199
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:26,800
I'm not going to waste
my time on you.

200
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:28,267
Felma...

201
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:29,833
- do you take Manuel...
- I do.

202
00:11:29,967 --> 00:11:31,833
- as your lawful...
- I do.

203
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:36,167
Sorry, I'm so sorry!

204
00:11:38,267 --> 00:11:39,467
And you, Manuel.

205
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,833
- Do you take Felma...
- I do! I do!

206
00:11:42,633 --> 00:11:46,633
Since you seem to be
in a hurry Manuel...

207
00:11:46,933 --> 00:11:48,833
You can kiss the bride now.

208
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:53,567
You may kiss the bride.

209
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:07,533
Love...

210
00:12:07,667 --> 00:12:10,333
I'm finally able to fulfill
my promise to you.

211
00:12:11,533 --> 00:12:13,200
To marry you.

212
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:15,367
From now on...

213
00:12:15,767 --> 00:12:17,533
you are my one...

214
00:12:17,667 --> 00:12:22,967
and only...

215
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:24,833
Mrs. Cruz.

216
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:39,833
That bastard ruined my plan.

217
00:12:40,533 --> 00:12:42,833
But it's fine.

218
00:12:42,967 --> 00:12:46,267
Even if I didn't get to stop
the wedding,

219
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:49,367
the two of you
will never be happy.

220
00:12:49,533 --> 00:12:51,167
Do you know why?

221
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:56,400
Because you will only be
Mrs. Cruz for a short while.

222
00:12:56,533 --> 00:12:58,900
Because I will make sure

223
00:12:59,033 --> 00:13:01,133
that Manuel
will be a widower soon.

224
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,467
You monster!

225
00:13:05,133 --> 00:13:07,733
Die, Felma! Die!

226
00:13:07,867 --> 00:13:09,433
Die!

227
00:13:32,900 --> 00:13:33,900
The fire has been put out.

228
00:13:34,033 --> 00:13:35,667
Thankfully,
it hasn't spread out.

229
00:13:35,933 --> 00:13:36,967
Have you seen Felma?

230
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:39,933
I'm sorry, Sir,
but I didn't see her.

231
00:13:40,067 --> 00:13:41,733
Kiana, have you seen my mom?

232
00:13:41,867 --> 00:13:42,733
No, Ma'am.

233
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,333
Where is she?

234
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:49,567
Wait, I thought I saw her
earlier at the parking area.

235
00:13:49,867 --> 00:13:51,000
Where?

236
00:13:51,133 --> 00:13:53,333
Sir, Sir Manuel!

237
00:13:53,467 --> 00:13:56,333
I saw Ma'am
Felma with Hazel.

238
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:58,100
What?

239
00:13:58,233 --> 00:14:01,033
I tried to follow her.

240
00:14:01,167 --> 00:14:02,767
But I'm not sure
if it's really her.

241
00:14:03,100 --> 00:14:06,967
I could be hallucinating since
I've inhaled a lot of smoke.

242
00:14:07,367 --> 00:14:09,333
What should we do?

243
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:11,467
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

244
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:14,400
Mr. Cruz, we're really
sorry about what happened.

245
00:14:14,533 --> 00:14:17,067
We called the police
to investigate.

246
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:19,700
Let's head to the banquet
hall so we can talk.

247
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:21,900
Take care of the
guests first.

248
00:14:22,033 --> 00:14:24,167
- Okay, Sir.
- Daisy, go with them.

249
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:27,067
Dad, you have to find
Mama Pretty.

250
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,067
Sweetie.

251
00:14:30,533 --> 00:14:33,233
- Take care of her, okay?
- Be careful, okay?

252
00:14:35,567 --> 00:14:37,300
- Didang.
- Yes?

253
00:14:37,433 --> 00:14:38,367
Come with us.

254
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:40,000
Show us where you saw Felma.

255
00:14:40,133 --> 00:14:41,367
This way, Sir Noah.

256
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:46,167
Get up, Felma.

257
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:48,733
I said, get up!

258
00:14:48,867 --> 00:14:53,567
Get up!

259
00:15:04,567 --> 00:15:05,867
You're so stubborn!

260
00:15:14,267 --> 00:15:16,333
Come with me! This way!

261
00:15:16,467 --> 00:15:18,767
- This is where I saw them!
- Are you sure?

262
00:15:18,900 --> 00:15:19,500
- Yes, Sir.
- Mom!

263
00:15:19,667 --> 00:15:20,800
Right here.

264
00:15:20,933 --> 00:15:22,000
Felma!

265
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:25,600
She's not here, Manuel.

266
00:15:25,733 --> 00:15:27,767
That's where I saw them.
I saw them there!

267
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:29,567
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

268
00:15:32,067 --> 00:15:34,233
What if Hazel
escaped from prison?

269
00:15:37,633 --> 00:15:39,333
I'm going to call
Colonel Sarabia.

270
00:15:41,367 --> 00:15:43,500
Jeff, Abel. Come with me.

271
00:15:43,633 --> 00:15:45,000
Let's look for Felma.

272
00:15:57,800 --> 00:16:00,533
Alonso, you
have to help me.

273
00:16:00,667 --> 00:16:02,467
I can't get out of this place!

274
00:16:04,667 --> 00:16:06,733
Room 206.

275
00:16:06,867 --> 00:16:08,167
Yes, at the resort.

276
00:16:10,333 --> 00:16:12,533
Yes, do something. Okay?

277
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:14,800
That's why I'm telling you!

278
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:22,300
It's an unknown number.

279
00:16:25,467 --> 00:16:26,767
Answer it.

280
00:16:28,667 --> 00:16:29,600
Hello?

281
00:16:29,733 --> 00:16:30,800
Manuel.

282
00:16:30,933 --> 00:16:32,067
Felma? Love?

283
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:34,400
- Where are you?
- That's what I'm saying...

284
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:38,600
Hey! What's that?

285
00:16:38,733 --> 00:16:40,467
What are you doing?

286
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:41,500
Manuel!

287
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:42,767
- I'm here at room 2...
- What are you doing?

288
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:43,967
- What's that?
- Manuel!

289
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:45,867
Hello, love?

290
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,167
- We're here at room...
- Is that you?

291
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:53,700
Hello, love?

292
00:16:53,833 --> 00:16:54,667
Love!

293
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:55,967
You monster!

294
00:16:58,867 --> 00:17:00,267
I'm going to kill you!

295
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:01,367
You animal!

296
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:02,433
Dad?

297
00:17:03,567 --> 00:17:05,600
Is Hazel with Mom?

298
00:17:07,767 --> 00:17:10,800
I just spoke with
Colonel Sarabia.

299
00:17:10,933 --> 00:17:14,000
Hazel escaped
prison two days ago.

300
00:17:20,267 --> 00:17:22,733
I'm going to kill
you, you animal!

301
00:17:22,867 --> 00:17:24,933
You really want
to get me in trouble!

302
00:17:25,067 --> 00:17:26,533
I will kill you now.
Is that what you want?

303
00:17:26,667 --> 00:17:27,833
I will kill you!

304
00:17:27,967 --> 00:17:29,133
Die!

305
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,767
Okay, Colonel,
you have to come here.

306
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:34,467
You're close by. Right?

307
00:17:35,867 --> 00:17:37,200
Thank you, Sir.

308
00:17:37,433 --> 00:17:38,767
Okay.

309
00:17:39,733 --> 00:17:42,067
Why does no one know that
Hazel escaped from prison?

310
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:46,267
We were all busy preparing
for your wedding.

311
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:50,600
I should have kept watch,
stayed focused.

312
00:17:50,767 --> 00:17:53,400
This wouldn't
have happened!

313
00:17:53,533 --> 00:17:55,567
This is all my fault!

314
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:58,200
If Hazel harms Felma,

315
00:17:58,467 --> 00:18:01,000
God forbid, but I will kill her!

316
00:18:01,133 --> 00:18:03,867
Dad, calm down.

317
00:18:08,267 --> 00:18:11,033
Die, Felma! Die!

318
00:18:11,167 --> 00:18:13,933
You're so stubborn!

319
00:18:25,067 --> 00:18:28,233
You're insane! You have to stop!

320
00:18:28,367 --> 00:18:30,567
Do you remember what
you told me before?

321
00:18:32,633 --> 00:18:37,100
<i>You will pay for everything
you've done to my family.</i>

322
00:18:37,233 --> 00:18:39,600
<i> And you will be forgotten.</i>

323
00:18:39,733 --> 00:18:44,033
<i> Like dirt,</i>

324
00:18:44,267 --> 00:18:48,467
<i>a stain
that got to my family once.</i>

325
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,667
Darn you!

326
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:44,067
Sorry!

327
00:19:46,433 --> 00:19:48,033
Sorry!

328
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:49,433
I'm sorry.

329
00:19:51,833 --> 00:19:53,333
Sorry!

330
00:19:55,567 --> 00:19:56,700
Sorry!

331
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:06,700
Sorry! Look, you got stains
on your dress!

332
00:20:07,367 --> 00:20:12,433
I see your face every day.

333
00:20:12,700 --> 00:20:14,700
I've dreamed of...

334
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:17,300
torturing you.

335
00:20:17,433 --> 00:20:19,633
I will take away your dignity.

336
00:20:19,900 --> 00:20:24,533
Until you think
that it's better to die.

337
00:20:24,667 --> 00:20:28,533
And you will beg me to kill you.

338
00:20:28,667 --> 00:20:31,233
You can't scare me
with your threats.

339
00:20:31,367 --> 00:20:33,867
Who says I'm threatening you?

340
00:20:35,933 --> 00:20:38,400
Why is this happening to us?

341
00:20:39,167 --> 00:20:40,933
When will this end?

342
00:20:41,967 --> 00:20:43,867
Everything's fine,
we're finally happy.

343
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:46,100
We've finally had
our fresh start.

344
00:20:50,267 --> 00:20:52,267
I know, come on.

345
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,033
There they are.

346
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:57,233
Happy anniversary!

347
00:20:57,367 --> 00:20:59,200
Congrats!

348
00:20:59,333 --> 00:21:00,467
- Awesome.
- Thank you.

349
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:01,733
Congrats!

350
00:21:01,867 --> 00:21:05,567
- Congrats, bro.
- Happy anniversary.

351
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:06,700
Are they here yet?

352
00:21:06,833 --> 00:21:08,433
Let's go inside.

353
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:09,367
Wait.

354
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:12,100
I have to take this call.

355
00:21:12,233 --> 00:21:13,233
Hello, Attorney Yeban.

356
00:21:14,333 --> 00:21:15,767
Yes, Attorney.

357
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:17,133
Really?

358
00:21:17,267 --> 00:21:18,800
Thank you so much.

359
00:21:18,933 --> 00:21:19,800
Okay.

360
00:21:20,900 --> 00:21:25,000
Kids, they granted me the
annulment from Hazel!

361
00:21:27,733 --> 00:21:30,367
We can go through
with our plans now!

362
00:21:31,767 --> 00:21:33,633
I will marry your mother!

363
00:21:39,567 --> 00:21:40,833
Where are you, Felma?

364
00:21:44,933 --> 00:21:46,067
Yes, Colonel?

365
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,333
Yes, Sir?

366
00:21:47,467 --> 00:21:48,700
Yes.

367
00:22:01,767 --> 00:22:05,400
Manuel, this is Colonel Sarabia.

368
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:08,767
We spotted a vehicle associated
with Hazel's friend.

369
00:22:09,667 --> 00:22:12,433
Alice Martinez is in the area.

370
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:14,267
Hazel is still here.

371
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:15,967
She hasn't left this area.

372
00:22:17,967 --> 00:22:19,800
Please find Felma.

373
00:22:22,133 --> 00:22:23,733
Men!

374
00:22:23,867 --> 00:22:25,600
Secure the perimeter!

375
00:22:25,733 --> 00:22:28,200
Quietly bring the guests
to the safe area.

376
00:22:28,467 --> 00:22:31,400
No panic, no announcements.

377
00:22:31,533 --> 00:22:35,200
Sweep every structure, room,

378
00:22:35,333 --> 00:22:39,367
service corridors,
service areas, utility areas!

379
00:22:39,667 --> 00:22:42,600
I want eyes on every corner
of this resort!

380
00:22:42,733 --> 00:22:43,767
Do you copy?

381
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:45,300
Sir, yes, Sir!

382
00:22:45,433 --> 00:22:47,767
Drone up in 60! Move!

383
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,500
- Manuel!
- Hey!

384
00:22:52,633 --> 00:22:54,000
- Love!
- Mom!

385
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:01,900
No clean shot, Sir!
We can breach the room.

386
00:23:02,033 --> 00:23:03,867
Do not go inside
without my permission.

387
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,533
Colonel, why did you
let them do that?

388
00:23:05,667 --> 00:23:06,833
It's too risky, Manuel.

389
00:23:06,967 --> 00:23:09,600
What she needs now
is someone to talk to.

390
00:23:09,733 --> 00:23:11,233
And that's where I come in.

391
00:23:11,367 --> 00:23:13,667
Meet police
Captain Antonette Ferrer,

392
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:15,367
Lead Negotiations Officer.

393
00:23:15,500 --> 00:23:16,533
You witch!

394
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:20,833
You're pissing me off!
I should kill you!

395
00:23:20,967 --> 00:23:22,067
I will kill you!

396
00:23:22,233 --> 00:23:23,167
I will...
